<div id="review_655841645" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/655841645" />
    <a title="Beth Meginness" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18123716-beth-meginness"><img alt="Beth Meginness" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1362616792p2/18123716.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/655841645?book_show_action=true">Jul 01, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Beth Meginness" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Beth Meginness" href="/user/show/18123716-beth-meginness">Beth Meginness</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18123716-beth-meginness?shelf=2013">2013</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer655841645" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7961051121468122819">Although this is a novel, the author must have first hand knowledge of living with a manic-depressive person. My daughter was finally diagnosed with Bipolar 1 disorder at the age of 20 after years of progressively worsening manic swings. We did not have the advantage of having a psychiatrist in the family, as in the book. In fact, while trying to seek help for her when I first realized that her mood swings were far more than just teenage angst, her MD led me to believe that it was my bad parenti</span>
  <span id="freeText7961051121468122819" style="display:none">Although this is a novel, the author must have first hand knowledge of living with a manic-depressive person. My daughter was finally diagnosed with Bipolar 1 disorder at the age of 20 after years of progressively worsening manic swings. We did not have the advantage of having a psychiatrist in the family, as in the book. In fact, while trying to seek help for her when I first realized that her mood swings were far more than just teenage angst, her MD led me to believe that it was my bad parenting that led to her behavior, not a mental illness on her part. I suspect this happens many times as this disorder is so vague at first. Our family journey closely followed the family in the novel, especially the descriptions of how the mom felt (since I experienced that first hand. Thankfully our daughter has not been hospitalized....yet. With this disease, one never knows when the next shoe will drop.<br /><br />A must read for anyone who wants to understand what living with a bipolar person is like.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7961051121468122819" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


